    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-05-13T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-05-13T17:00:00-05:00" n="283"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d283">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">632.003/196: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-05-13T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 13, 1936—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>70. For Gibson from Welles. Your 123, May 10, 5 p.m. I have had the matter of the
                    2 per cent tax very carefully studied by the Department’s competent advisers,
                    all of whom, after a careful reexamination, are convinced of the soundness of
                    their original conclusions. I appreciate that the Embassy may be caused some
                    embarrassment and that the Department may be subjected to criticism by business
                    interests based upon their misapprehension of the terms of the agreement, but
                    hope that perhaps by pointing out that the tax is contrary to the general policy
                    of expanding trade through reduction of tariff barriers espoused by both
                    Governments in the Trade Agreement, the Brazilian Government may decide to
                    abolish it. [Welles.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
